Make sure you have the appropriate dependencies in your project's build configuration to use Jakarta Persistence. For example, in Maven, you would need the following dependency:

```xml
<dependency>
    <groupId>jakarta.persistence</groupId>
    <artifactId>jakarta.persistence-api</artifactId>
    <version>3.0.0</version>
</dependency>
```
Similarly, for Gradle, you can add the dependency as follows:

```groovy
implementation 'jakarta.persistence:jakarta.persistence-api:3.0.0'
```

Ensure the version specified in the dependency aligns with the Jakarta Persistence version you intend to use.

By updating the imports and dependencies to use `jakarta.persistence`, you will be able to use the appropriate annotations and APIs for mapping entities with Hibernate in your Jakarta EE or Jakarta Persistence project.

