The error you encountered suggests that the `CouchbaseConfig` class must either be declared as an abstract class or implement the abstract method `getConnectionString()` from the `AbstractCouchbaseConfiguration` class.

To resolve this issue, you can follow these steps:

1. Ensure that you are using the correct version of `spring-data-couchbase` library, compatible with your version of Couchbase and Spring Boot.

2. Make sure that your `CouchbaseConfig` class extends `AbstractCouchbaseConfiguration` provided by the `spring-data-couchbase` library.

3. Override the `getConnectionString()` method in your `CouchbaseConfig` class and provide the necessary implementation. For example:

```java
import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Value;
import org.springframework.context.annotation.Configuration;
import org.springframework.data.couchbase.config.AbstractCouchbaseConfiguration;

@Configuration
public class CouchbaseConfig extends AbstractCouchbaseConfiguration {

    @Value("${couchbase.cluster.bucket}")
    private String bucketName;

    @Value("${couchbase.cluster.password}")
    private String password;

    @Value("${couchbase.cluster.host}")
    private String host;

    @Override
    protected String getConnectionString() {
        return "couchbase://" + host;
    }

    @Override
    protected String getUserName() {
        return bucketName;
    }

    @Override
    protected String getPassword() {
        return password;
    }

    @Override
    protected String getBucketName() {
        return bucketName;
    }
}
```

Ensure that you are providing appropriate values for `bucketName`, `password`, and `host` properties by either specifying them in the application.properties/application.yml file or using other configuration methods.

By implementing the `getConnectionString()` method and providing the necessary information, you should be able to resolve the mentioned error and proceed with your project setup.

